Merge pull request #4653 from ichorid/f_channel_gossip_versions

Check timestamp of entry against the channel ver
Make GigaChannel nodes id_ random

Check timestamp of entry against the channel ver

Timestamps of incoming GigaChannel payloads are now checked
against the parent channel's local_version. This allows
us to stop getting old deleted results from previous channel
versions.
Also, fixed a severe bug in channel commit procedure. When committing
the personal channel, mdblob files should only contain entries with
timestamps <= to the mdblob filename, but the last mdblob must have
the same timestamp as the channel entry itself. Before, this was only
true if the channel entry was never edited (e.g. renamed) before commit.
Now we assign filenames based on the timestamp of the last entry in the
mdblob, except for the last file. For this, we create a new timestamp,
and then assign it to _both_ the filename and the updated channel entry.

GigaChannel Community gossip caching

GigaChannel Community gossip caching

This makes GigaChannel Community cache the results of the SQL query
that selects the channel contents to gossip around. The resulting
blob is saved for reuse in the Community object. The blob will be sent
to 30 peers, and then the new query will be performed. This
significantly reduces the background DB activity.

Merge pull request #4581 from ichorid/f_tmp_files_sqlite3

Fix horrible disk churn in converter

Fix horrible disk churn in converter

Converter query for getting old entries from the legacy database
creates and deletes several temporary files in /tmp/var/etilqs*
for *each* fetched row.
This amounts to gigabytes of useless disk writes on Linux during
conversion of a big database.
This patch disables usage of temporary files by Sqlite3 wrapper
during 7.2.2->Pony conversion.

add lz4, fix timestamp resolution problem

This commit adds support for lz4 compression of mdblobs. Squashed
mdblobs are now compressed by default, both on disk and when sent
through the gossip community. In addition, this commit fixes the problem
where metadata timestamp was incorrectly coerced to float from double on
serialization. To simplify updating the tests on metdata format change,
a simple script to regenerate tests is added.

Rework GUI to support GigaChannel

This patch replaces QT List-based view of the channels and their
contents with a TableView-based widget that uses QT MVC idiom.
The provided TableModel is capable of loading data lazily from the
REST endpoint. The corresponding endpoint is modified to send the
data in small pages and do sorts and searches. The TableView
serves the model with a custom Delegate.

Made copy of destinations dict to prevent crash

The destinations set is modified within a while loop. The iteritems method constructs an iterator which will fail if the dictionary changes size during iteration. I changed the iteritems to items, so it makes a copy instead. This method is not invoked frequently (only when a circuit breaks) so it should not impact anonymous download performance.

returns active (i.e. stumble and walk) candidates, hence no introduced
candidates were ever walked too.  Effectively disabling the fast
walker.

- prematurely abort fast walk when 20 active candidates are available

encoding.py is no longer provided by Dispersy,

The file encoding.py is used by several communities, however it is not
used by Dispersy.  When Dispersy needs functionality such as is
provided by encoding.py, it will use binary encoding or a more
standard encoding such as json instead.

To ensure none of the existing code breaks, encoding.py has moved into
the Tribler reprository.
